The paper deals with Reeb graphs, which are a fundamental tool in computational geometry and topology. The focus is on defining a combinatorial metric for Reeb graphs of orientable surfaces, which suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses stability and optimality properties of the edit distance, which are concepts that are often studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also mentions applications of Reeb graphs in computer vision and image processing, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on structural descriptors and shape properties suggests that it could also belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
